article.description:
Vickie Johnson scored 20 points and Tamika Whitmore added 19 as the New York Liberty defeated the Miami Sol
66-54 Friday night.
article.headline: Liberty atop East, Sol in playoff jeopardy
article.linkText: Liberty have first to themselves after eclipsing Sol
article.story:
NEW YORK (AP) -- Vickie Johnson scored 20 points and Tamika Whitmore added 19 as the New York Liberty defeated the Miami Sol 66-54 Friday night. Tari Phillips added 14 points and Teresa Weatherspoon had 10 assists for the Liberty (16-10), who moved into sole possession of first place in the Eastern Conference. New York, winners of six of seven, moved ahead of the Washington Mystics by one game with six games left in the season. The struggling Mystics lost 67-65 to Portland on Friday. Kristen Rasmussen scored a career-high 19 points, the only player in double figures for the Sol (12-16), who fell two games behind Orlando for the final playoff spot in the East. Miami, which has lost four of five on its road trip, shot 35 percent and was outrebounded 34-27. The Liberty opened the second half with a 14-0 run to lead 47-30 before reserve Iziane Castro Marques' layup ended Miami's 5-minute scoring drought. Johnson scored 10 in the spurt, including two 3-pointers. Ruth Riley's consecutive baskets trimmed the lead to 50-41 with 10 minutes left, but the Sol could get no closer. Whitmore's free throws extended the lead to 61-48 with just over three minutes remaining. The Liberty won their sixth straight at Madison Square Garden before a crowd of 17,344 and improved to 5-4 in the regular-season series against the Sol. Johnson finished 6-for-9 from the field, including 4-for-6 from behind the arch. Weatherspoon tied her season high with seven rebounds. Rasmussen, who had 12 first-half points on 5-of-6 shooting, capped the Sol's 7-0 run with a 3-point play to trail 24-22 with 3:51 left. Phillips' turnaround 10-footer gave the Liberty a 33-30 halftime lead. Game notes
Whitmore shot 53 percent in July, averaging 14.8 points and 6.0 rebounds in nine games. ... The Liberty went 7-2 last month, losing to Miami 54-46 and last-place Detroit 66-63. ... New York plays three of its final six games at home. ... Miami missed 10 of 11 shots to start the game. ... The Sol lost by an average of 9.0 points in their five-game road trip. ... On banner night, some New York fans held "Lesbians for Liberty'' signs to protest an alleged lack of acknowledgment of a segment of its fan base from Liberty management.
